summary: The customer was disconnected from a previous call and wants to continue the discussion with a company executive about a package detail that was not properly provided to them. The executive helps the customer register a complaint and also forwards their query to the package details department. The customer also requests to get the wrapper sent to them and receives a complaint number (1753) and a WhatsApp number (9606 9606) from the executive before ending the call.
speaker_a_summary: An individual gets transferred to a new executive as the previous one disconnected. The new executive is trying to help the individual with an issue they were having, however the executive is having trouble as they only have a partial package on hand and they need more details from the individual in order to proceed. The individual is trying to help the executive as best they can, but they are also having some difficulty. The issue is eventually resolved and the call ends.
speaker_b_summary: The customer is calling to register a complaint. They are missing one or more items from a package they received which weighed 5kg or 10kg and had an MRP of 390. They are also missing the packaging and are prompted to provide their complaint number (1753 fiv 753521), and their WhatsApp number (2606 9606). The customer is advised that a member of the executive team will visit their location within 4-5 days and that they will need to provide the package details.
